<item>
<title>Huawei’s HarmonyOS to beat Apple’s IOS as the No. 2 smartphone operating system in China in 2024: TechInsights report</title>
<link>https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3247172/huaweis-harmonyos-beat-apples-ios-no-2-smartphone-operating-system-china-2024-techinsights-report</link>
<description><![CDATA[ <div>  <h2>Summary：</h2>  HarmonyOS，华为自研操作系统，预计今年将超越苹果iOS，成为中国第二大操作系统。 华为重返5G智能手机市场，以及美国制裁后Mate 60系列的发布，是HarmonyOS采用率增长的主要推动力。 HarmonyOS表现亮眼，在智能手机操作系统全球市场中，谷歌Android和苹果iOS依然占据主导地位，但HarmonyOS将在中国市场从这两大巨头手中抢占一些份额。   <ul>    <li>Abstract: Increased HarmonyOS adoption expected with Huawei's return to 5G smartphone segment.</li>    <li>Theme: HarmonyOS, Huawei's self-developed operating system, is projected to surpass Apple's iOS, becoming the second-biggest in China.</li>    <li>Viewpoint: US sanctions and the launch of the Mate 60 series drive HarmonyOS adoption; potential impact on other smartphone makers and expansion to other devices.</li>    <li>Main information: HarmonyOS's current market position; Huawei's comeback in the 5G smartphone segment; supply challenges and recovery; plans for HarmonyOS Next and developer recruitment.</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>总结：</h2>  HarmonyOS，华为自研操作系统，预计今年将超越苹果iOS，成为中国第二大操作系统。华为重返5G智能手机市场，以及美国制裁后Mate 60系列的发布，是HarmonyOS采用率增长的主要推动力。HarmonyOS表现亮眼，在智能手机操作系统全球市场中，谷歌Android和苹果iOS依然占据主导地位，但HarmonyOS将在中国市场从这两大巨头手中抢占一些份额。  <ul>    <li>摘要：HarmonyOS采用率增加，主要是由于华为重返5G智能手机市场。</li>    <li>主题：HarmonyOS超越iOS，成为中国第二大操作系统。</li>    <li>观点：美国制裁和Mate 60系列发布推动了HarmonyOS采用率的增长；对其他智能手机制造商的潜在影响以及扩展到其他设备的可能性。</li>    <li>主要信息：HarmonyOS当前的市场地位；华为在5G智能手机市场的复苏；供应挑战和复苏；HarmonyOS Next的计划和开发者招募。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>单词：</h2>  <ul>    <li>handset (n.) - /ˈhændˌsɛt/ 手持式电话，话筒。    <p>原文例句：The Mate 60 Pro is a handset equipped with an advanced, home-grown 5G chip despite US tech sanctions intended to block access to such technology. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词由hand（手）和set（放置）组成，表示“手持式电话，话筒”。在这个例句中，它指的是Mate 60 Pro，即配备了先进的国产5G芯片的手持式电话，尽管美国科技制裁旨在阻止获取此类技术。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>developer (n.) - /dɪˈvɛləpər/ 开发者，研制者。    <p>原文例句：Huawei is already working with China’s major companies to develop native apps based on the system. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词由develop（发展，开发）和-er（表示从事某项工作的人）构成，表示“开发者，研制者”。在这个例句中，它指的是华为正在与中国主要公司合作，基于HarmonyOS系统开发原生应用程序的开发者。</p></li>  </ul>  </div><div>  <h2>词组：</h2>  <ul>    <li>self-developed - 自主研发的，自力更生的。    <P>原文例句：Huawei’s smartphones are all powered by HarmonyOS, its self-developed Android alternative launched in August 2019, three months after the US government added the firm to its Entity List. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组是由self（自我，自身）和developed（开发，研制）构成的，表示“自主研发的，自力更生的”。在这个例句中，它指的是华为手机都搭载HarmonyOS，这是华为在2019年8月推出的自主研发的Android替代品，三个月后美国政府将华为列入实体名单。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>句子：</h2>  <ul>    <li>Huawei Technologies’ mobile platform HarmonyOS is projected to surpass Apple’s IOS as the second-biggest operating system in China this year driven by the US-sanctioned firm’s comeback with the Mate 60 series, according to a report by TechInsights. - 据TechInsights报告，华为的技术移动平台HarmonyOS预计今年将超越苹果的iOS，成为中国第二大操作系统，这得益于这家受到美国制裁的公司推出Mate 60系列手机重返市场。<p>句子分析：这是一个复杂的句子，有四个分句和一个主句。主句是Huawei Technologies’ mobile platform HarmonyOS is projected to surpass Apple’s IOS as the second-biggest operating system in China this year，其中主语是Huawei Technologies’ mobile platform HarmonyOS，谓语是is projected to surpass，宾语是Apple’s IOS。第一个分句是driven by the US-sanctioned firm’s comeback with the Mate 60 series，其中driven by是过去分词短语作状语，表示原因或理由，the US-sanctioned firm’s comeback with the Mate 60 series是名词性短语作主语，表示美国受到制裁的公司带着Mate 60系列手机重返市场。第二个分句是according to a report by TechInsights，其中according to是介词短语作状语，表示根据，a report by TechInsights是名词性短语作主语，表示TechInsights的一份报告。这个句子的意思是说，据TechInsights报告，华为的技术移动平台HarmonyOS预计今年将超越苹果的iOS，成为中国第二大操作系统，这得益于这家受到美国制裁的公司推出Mate 60系列手机重返市场。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>语法：</h2>  <ul>    <li>强调句型 - 用于强调句子中的某个成分。    <p>原文例句：HarmonyOS is also projected to reach a milestone in 2024 with the launch of HarmonyOS Next, which will not support Android-based apps.</p>    <p>语法讲解：强调句型是一种特殊的句子结构，用来强调句子中的某个成分。强调句型的结构是：It is/was + 被强调的成分 + that/who + 其他成分。在这个例句中，被强调的成分是HarmonyOS Next，所以强调句的结构是：It is HarmonyOS Next that will not support Android-based apps。这个句子的意思是说，HarmonyOS Next预计将在2024年发布，它不支持基于Android的应用程序。</p></li>  </ul>   <ul>    <li>虚拟语气 - 表示假设、愿望、建议、请求等。    <p>原文例句：Huawei is expected to launch a developer preview version of HarmonyOS Next in the first quarter of 2024. </p>    <p>语法讲解：虚拟语气是一种特殊的语态，用于表示假设、愿望、建议、请求等。虚拟语气的结构是：should/could/would/may/might + 动词原形。在这个例句中，is expected to launch是虚拟语气的结构，表示华为预计将在2024年第一季度发布HarmonyOS Next的开发者预览版。</p></li>  </ul></div>  <ul><li>Increased HarmonyOS adoption is expected to be driven by Huawei’s return to the 5G smartphone segment</li>
<li>TechInsights also expects Huawei’s supply challenge, driven by shortages of Kirin 9000s chipsets, to ease in the next few months</li>
</ul><figure><img src="https://cdn.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/d8/images/canvas/2024/01/03/83c4b156-87f3-4acb-b3f4-8cb885281387_c0009114.jpg" /><figcaption>Increased HarmonyOS adoption will be driven by Huawei’s return to the 5G smartphone segment. Photo: Shutterstock </figcaption></figure><p>Huawei Technologies’ mobile platform HarmonyOS is projected to surpass Apple’s IOS as the second-biggest operating system in China this year driven by the US-sanctioned firm’s comeback with the Mate 60 series, according to a report by TechInsights.</p><p>While Google’s Android and Apple’s IOS will continue to dominate the global smartphone operating system sector, Huawei’s self-developed HarmonyOS will take some ground from both US giants in China, Canadian research firm TechInsights said in a report released on Wednesday.</p><p>Increased HarmonyOS adoption will be driven by Huawei’s return to the 5G smartphone segment, which started with the surprise launch in late August of its Mate 60 Pro, a handset equipped with an advanced, home-grown 5G chip despite US tech sanctions intended to block access to such technology.</p><p>TechInsights also expects Huawei to make a solid recovery in 2024, according to the report.</p><p>Huawei’s smartphones are all powered by HarmonyOS, its self-developed Android alternative launched in August 2019, three months after the US government <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3012321/huawei-among-more-140-chinese-entities-us-trade-blacklist?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">added the firm to its Entity List</a>. Under this trade blacklist, Huawei is barred from buying software, chips and other US-origin technologies from suppliers without Washington’s approval.</p><p>On its release, the Mate 60 Pro inspired <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/tech-war/article/3233514/tech-war-huawei-helps-china-win-symbolic-victory-defying-washingtons-sanctions-headwinds-remain?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">a wave of patriotic fervour</a> among Chinese consumers, and the Shenzhen-based firm <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3241541/huawei-has-big-problem-popular-mate-60-5g-smartphones-theres-not-enough-supply-meet-growing-demand" target="_self" title="">faced supply issues as it scrambled to crank up production to meet demand</a>.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/article/3246566/huawei-sees-9-cent-sales-growth-2023-it-bounces-back-us-sanctions-cautions-serious-challenges-ahead" title="">Huawei sees 9 per cent sales growth in 2023, boosted by Mate 60 Pro 5G comeback</a></h3><p>TechInsights expects Huawei’s supply challenge, driven by shortages of Kirin 9000s chipsets, to ease in the next few months. Huawei’s product portfolio further expanded last week when it launched new smartphone models under its mid-range Nova series.</p><p>HarmonyOS is also projected to reach a milestone in 2024 with the launch of HarmonyOS Next, which will not support Android-based apps.</p><p>Huawei is expected to launch a developer preview version of HarmonyOS Next in the first quarter of 2024, and is already working with China’s major companies to develop native apps based on the system.</p><p>Last month, Chinese financial technology giant Ant Group, the fintech affiliate of South China Morning Post owner <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/alibaba?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">Alibaba Group Holding</a>, said it is building a new version of mobile payment app Alipay based on HarmonyOS, after <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3242703/alibaba-develops-native-dingtalk-app-harmonyos-huawei-aims-end-support-android-apps?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">Alibaba started development on a new version of DingTalk</a>, its workplace collaboration app, for the platform.</p><p>Other major Chinese <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/internet?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">internet</a> companies – including e-commerce firm <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/jdcom?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">JD.com</a>, video gaming giant <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/netease?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">NetEase</a> and food delivery market leader <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/meituan?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">Meituan</a> – in November already started to <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3241371/chinese-big-tech-firms-jdcom-netease-and-meituan-rush-hire-harmonyos-based-app-developers-huawei?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">recruit developers to build native apps for HarmonyOS</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/mcdonalds?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">McDonald’s</a> China – with a network of more than 5,500 restaurants and over 200,000 employees serving more than 1 billion customers each year – became <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3244236/mcdonalds-china-pushes-development-native-apps-based-harmonyos-adoption-huaweis-mobile-operating?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">one of the first multinational food companies on the mainland to adopt</a> <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3239589/xiaomi-launches-home-grown-cross-device-system-hyperos-us-sanctioned-huawei-moves-further-googles?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">HarmonyOS Next</a>.</p><p>It remains to be seen whether these efforts will have a halo effect on other smartphone makers and make HarmonyOS a default operating system for not just smartphones but also laptops and cars in China, TechInsights said.</p><p>More than 700 million devices currently run on HarmonyOS, with more than 2.2 million third-party developers creating apps for the platform, according to Richard Yu Chengdong, CEO of Huawei’s consumer business group, speaking at the company’s <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3230293/tech-war-huawei-revive-smartphone-business-back-fresh-ai-powered-operating-system-even-us-sanctions?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">annual developer conference in August</a>.</p> ]]></description>
</item>

<item>
<title>Apple dominates global premium smartphone market in 2023, but Huawei gains ground on the back of its new 5G handsets</title>
<link>https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3247159/apple-dominates-global-premium-smartphone-market-2023-huawei-gains-ground-back-its-new-5g-handsets</link>
<description><![CDATA[ <div>  <h2>Summary：</h2>  Apple continued to be the world's leading vendor of premium smartphones in 2023, with a whopping 71% market share, but its dominance saw a decline compared to the previous year. This was partly attributed to Huawei's comeback in the 5G segment with its Mate 60 series and the rising popularity of Samsung's foldable phones. Despite the market challenges and a projected decline in overall smartphone shipments globally, the premium segment remained resilient and accounted for a significant portion of industry revenue.   <ul>    <li>Abstract: Apple retains leadership in the premium smartphone market, facing competition from Huawei and Samsung.</li>    <li>Theme: Shifts in consumer buying patterns and the resilience of the premium smartphone segment amidst a declining overall market.</li>    <li>Viewpoint: The importance of high-quality devices in the premium segment and the role of promotion seasons and financing options in making these devices more accessible.</li>    <li>Main information: Apple's market share decline, Huawei's resurgence, Samsung's foldable phones' success, growth in emerging markets, and increasing affordability of premium smartphones.</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>总结：</h2>  苹果公司在2023年依然是全球高端智能手机的顶级供应商，拥有71%的市场份额，但其优势地位却同比下降。这部分原因归因于华为凭借其Mate 60系列在5G领域的回归，以及三星折叠屏手机的日益普及。尽管面临市场挑战以及全球智能手机出货量预计下降，高端智能手机市场仍然保持弹性，并在行业收入中占据了很大一部分。  <ul>    <li>摘要：苹果在高端智能手机市场保持领先地位，面临来自华为和三星的竞争。</li>    <li>主题：消费者购买模式的变化和在整体市场下降的情况下高端智能手机市场展示的稳健性。</li>    <li>观点：高端智能手机市场的高品质设备的重要性，以及促销季和金融选项在使这些设备更实惠中所扮演的角色。</li>    <li>主要信息：苹果市场份额的下降、华为的复苏、三星折叠屏手机的成功、新兴市场的发展以及高端智能手机越来越实惠。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>单词：</h2>  <ul>    <li>share (n.) - /ʃɛər/ 份额，シェア。    <p>原文例句：According to research firm Counterpoint, Apple remained the world’s top vendor of premium smartphones in 2023, with a 71 per cent market share. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词表示“份额，比例”，在这个例句中，它指的是苹果公司在2023年高端智能手机市场的份额为71%。</p></li>    <li>resurgence (n.) - /rɪˈsɜːrdʒ(ə)ns/ 复兴，复苏。    <p>原文例句：Apple’s share, however, was down from 75 per cent in 2022 amid the resurgence of Huawei, which released its first new 5G smartphones since October 2020.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词表示“复兴，复苏”，在这个例句中，它指的是华为在2020年10月发布了第一款新的5G智能手机后，在高端智能手机市场上的复苏。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>segment (n.) - /ˈsɛɡmənt/ 部分，领域。    <p>原文例句：Apple continued to lead the smartphone industry’s premium segment in 2023, but saw its worldwide share decline mainly because of US-sanctioned Huawei Technologies’ strong 5G handset market comeback with its Mate 60 series. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词表示“部分，领域”，在这个例句中，它指的是智能手机行业的细分市场。</p></li>  </ul>  </div><div>  <h2>词组：</h2>  <ul>    <li>projected decrease - 预计下降。    <p>原文例句：The global premium smartphone market, where handsets are priced from US$600, saw Apple remain the “undisputed leader” last year with a dominant 71 per cent share, according to the latest industry report released on Tuesday by Counterpoint Research.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组由project（预测）和decrease（减少）组成，表示“预测减少”。在这个例句中，它指的是全球高端智能手机市场的预计下降。</p>    <li>consumer buying patterns - 消费者购买模式。    <p>原文例句：“There has been a shift in consumer buying patterns in the smartphone market,” Counterpoint senior analyst Varun Mishra said in the premium segment report. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组由consumer（消费者）和buying patterns（购买模式）组成，表示“消费者购买模式”。在这个例句中，它指的是智能手机市场中消费者的购买模式的转变。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>句子：</h2>  <ul>    <li>Huawei Technologies’ Mate 60 Pro 5G smartphones are seen on display at an electronics store in Xian, capital of northwestern Shaanxi province, on September 9, 2023. Photo: Shutterstock - 华为Mate 60 Pro 5G智能手机于2023年9月9日在陕西省西北部首府西安市的一家电子商店展示。摄影：Shutterstock<p>句子分析：这是一个简单的陈述句，主语是Huawei Technologies’ Mate 60 Pro 5G smartphones，谓语是are seen，宾语是on display at an electronics store in Xian, capital of northwestern Shaanxi province。这个句子的意思是说，华为Mate 60 Pro 5G智能手机于2023年9月9日在陕西省西北部首府西安市的一家电子商店展示。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>语法：</h2>  <ul>    <li>分词短语 - 分词短语是由分词和修饰成分，表示事物不同的附加成分。分词短语可以用来修饰主语、宾语和状语，在句子中通常充当定语和状语。    <p>原文例句：According to research firm Counterpoint, Apple remained the world’s top vendor of premium smartphones in 2023, with a 71 per cent market share.</p>    <p>语法讲解：在"According to research firm Counterpoint"，"According to"是一个介词结构，"research firm Counterpoint"是一个名词短语，"According to research firm Counterpoint"是一个介词短语修饰了动词"remained"。</p></li>    <li>动词不定式 - 动词不定式是不带"to"的不定式，由动词原形加"ing"或"ed"构成。动词不定式可以作为名词、形容词和副词。    <p>原文例句：There has been a shift in consumer buying patterns in thesmartphone market,” Counterpoint senior analyst Varun Mishra said in the premium segment report.</p>    <p>语法讲解：在"There has been a shift..."，"There"是一个形式主语，"has been"是助动词，"a shift"是动名词，"in consumer buying patterns"是介词短语，"There has been a shift in consumer buying patterns"是一个完整的主语。动词不定式作为主语。</p></li>  </ul></div>  <ul><li>Apple remained the world’s top vendor of premium smartphones in 2023, with a 71 per cent market share, according to research firm Counterpoint</li>
<li>The US firm’s lead, however, declined year on year amid Huawei’s 5G comeback with its Mate 60 series and the gains made by Samsung’s foldable phones</li>
</ul><figure><img src="https://cdn.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/d8/images/canvas/2024/01/03/64d88f21-13d4-47d7-a021-0a71facc64d7_e98ebaba.jpg" /><figcaption>Apple’s iPhone 15 Pro and Pro Max models are seen on display at a store in Xian, capital of northwestern Shaanxi province, on September 22, 2023. Photo: Shutterstock</figcaption></figure><p><a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/apple" target="_self" title="">Apple</a> continued to lead the <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/smartphones" target="_self" title="">smartphone</a> industry’s premium segment in 2023, but saw its worldwide share decline mainly because of <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3012321/huawei-among-more-140-chinese-entities-us-trade-blacklist" target="_self" title="">US-sanctioned</a> <a href="https://www.scmp.com/knowledge/companies/huawei/news" target="_self" title="">Huawei Technologies</a>’ strong <a href="https://www.scmp.com/knowledge/topics/5g/news" target="_self" title="">5G</a> handset market comeback with its Mate 60 series.</p><p>The global premium smartphone market, where handsets are priced from US$600, saw Apple remain the “undisputed leader” last year with a dominant 71 per cent share, according to the latest industry report released on Tuesday by Counterpoint Research.</p><p>Apple’s share, however, was down from 75 per cent in 2022 amid the resurgence of Huawei, which <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3236295/huaweis-5g-smartphone-comeback-advanced-chip-wrapped-secrecy-releases-chokehold-us-sanctions-china?module=inline&amp;pgtype=article" target="_self" title="">released its first new 5G smartphones since October 2020</a>, as well as the gains made by <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/samsung-electronics" target="_self" title="">Samsung Electronics</a>’ Galaxy S23 series and its latest <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/foldable-phones" target="_self" title="">foldable phones</a>.</p><p>Samsung retained the global No 2 spot in the premium segment with a share of 17 per cent, compared to 16 per cent in 2022. Still, No 3 Huawei captured more new ground year on year with a 5 per cent share, up from 3 per cent in 2022, according to the Counterpoint report.</p><div class="image-inline-container"><figure><img alt="Huawei Technologies’ Mate 60 Pro 5G smartphones are seen on display at an electronics store in Xian, capital of northwestern Shaanxi province, on September 9, 2023. Photo: Shutterstock" class="image-inline caption" height="1333" src="https://cdn.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/d8/images/canvas/2024/01/03/cb3a9a4b-0ce5-45f4-91e6-798c2c4c40f0_5babf532.jpg" title="Huawei Technologies’ Mate 60 Pro 5G smartphones are seen on display at an electronics store in Xian, capital of northwestern Shaanxi province, on September 9, 2023. Photo: Shutterstock" width="2000" /><figcaption>Huawei Technologies’ Mate 60 Pro 5G smartphones are seen on display at an electronics store in Xian, capital of northwestern Shaanxi province, on September 9, 2023. Photo: Shutterstock</figcaption></figure></div><p><a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/xiaomi" target="_self" title="">Xiaomi</a> and <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/oppo" target="_self" title="">Oppo</a> last year took the fourth and fifth spots in the premium smartphone segment with a 2 per cent and 1 per cent share, respectively.</p><p>The latest market data shows the resilience of the premium segment, despite the projected decrease in the overall global smartphone market in 2023 – global handset shipments are forecast to hit their lowest level in almost a decade with a 5 per cent decline, according to an earlier Counterpoint report.</p><p>The premium segment, meanwhile, was expected to account for nearly one-fourth of global smartphone market sales and 60 per cent of the industry’s revenue in 2023. Counterpoint data shows that the so-called ultra-premium segment, where smartphones cost more than US$1,000, accounted for one-third of total premium handset sales last year.</p><p>Over the past few years, the premium segment has emerged as a growth area in the otherwise weak worldwide smartphone market. Counterpoint projected the premium segment sales share to triple to 24 per cent in 2023, compared to 6 per cent in 2016.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/gadgets/article/3246457/ranked-top-5-smartphones-2023-iphone-15-pro-max-and-google-pixel-8-pro-two-foldable-phones-and-best" title="">Top 5 smartphones of 2023, from iPhone 15 Pro Max to the best camera phone</a></h3><p>“There has been a shift in consumer buying patterns in the smartphone market,” Counterpoint senior analyst Varun Mishra said in the premium segment report. “Considering the importance a smartphone holds, consumers are willing to spend more to get a high-quality device that they can use for a longer period.”</p><p>Much of the global premium segment’s growth last year was driven by China, western Europe, <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/india" target="_self" title="">India</a>, and the Middle East-and-Africa regions, according to Counterpoint.</p><p>India is already the world’s fastest-growing market for premium smartphones, the Counterpoint report said. <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3217435/apple-opens-first-retail-store-india-us-tech-giant-sharpens-focus-south-asian-nation-major-market" target="_self" title="">Apple opened its first retail store in India</a> last April, underscoring the US tech titan’s increasing focus on the South Asian nation as a key sales market and alternative manufacturing hub to China.</p><p>“Owning the latest and greatest flagships has also become a status symbol for many consumers, especially in emerging markets where they are jumping directly from the mid-price band to the premium band,” Mishra said. “Further, these devices are increasingly becoming more affordable due to promotion seasons and financing options.”</p> ]]></description>
</item>

<item>
<title>ByteDance’s Douyin makes instant refunds mandatory, following PDD, Taobao and JD.com amid fierce e-commerce competition</title>
<link>https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3247160/bytedances-douyin-makes-instant-refunds-mandatory-following-pdd-taobao-and-jdcom-amid-fierce-e</link>
<description><![CDATA[ <div>  <h2>English summary：</h2>  In the fierce competition of e-commerce platforms in China, Douyin, the Chinese version of TikTok, has made its "express refund" policy mandatory. This forces merchants to immediately return money to consumers upon request in order to compete with similar offerings on Taobao and Pinduoduo. These platforms are turning to policies known as "refund without returning the cargo" or "refund without reason" to attract more consumers.    <ul>    <li>Abstract: Amid fierce competition, Douyin's mandatory "express refund" policy requires merchants to instantly return money to consumers, similar to policies on Taobao and Pinduoduo.</li>    <li>Theme: E-commerce platforms in China adopt customer-friendly policies like “refund without returning the cargo” to attract consumers.</li>    <li>Viewpoint: The importance of consumer-friendly policies in e-commerce; the impact of the mandatory refund policy on merchants.</li>    <li>Main information: Douyin's mandatory refund policy; similar policies on Taobao and Pinduoduo; increase in online retail sales in China; Alibaba's efforts to win back consumers.</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>中文总结：</h2>  在中国电商平台的激烈竞争中，抖音作为中国版的 TikTok，已使其“极速退款”政策强制执行。为了与淘宝和拼多多上类似的优惠活动竞争，这迫使商家在收到退货请求后立即将钱款退还给消费者。这些平台正在转向“无需退货退款”或“无理由退款”等政策，以吸引更多消费者。  <ul>    <li>摘要：在激烈的竞争中，抖音强制执行的“极速退款”政策要求商家立即向消费者退款，类似于淘宝和拼多多上的政策。</li>    <li>主题：中国电商平台采用“无需退货退款”等亲消费者政策来吸引消费者。</li>    <li>观点：消费者友好政策在电子商务中的重要性；强制退款政策对商家的影响。</li>    <li>主要信息：抖音的强制退款政策；淘宝和拼多多上的类似政策；中国在线零售额的增长；阿里巴巴为赢回消费者所做的努力。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>单词：</h2>  <ul>    <li>woo (v.) - 追求，吸引。    <p>原文例句：Alibaba’s Taobao and JD.com recently started offering refunds without returns to woo consumers away from rising budget e-commerce champion Pinduoduo.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于古英语单词wōh（求爱），表示“追求，吸引”。在这个例句中，它的意思是阿里巴巴的淘宝和京东最近开始提供无理由退款服务，以吸引消费者远离新兴的预算电商巨头拼多多。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>mandatory (adj.) - 强制的，必须的。    <p>原文例句：Douyin, the Chinese version of TikTok that is betting big on e-commerce, has made its “express refund” policy mandatory, forcing merchants to immediately return money to consumers upon request to compete with similar offerings on Taobao and Pinduoduo.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于Latin，由manus（手）和dare（给予）组成，表示“强迫，强制”。在这个例句中，它的意思是抖音，作为在中国电子商务领域押下重注的 TikTok 的中国版本，已经将其“极速退款”政策变成强制性的，迫使商家在收到退款请求后立即向消费者退款，以与淘宝和拼多多上类似的优惠活动竞争。</p></li>  </ul>  </div><div>  <h2>词组：</h2>  <ul>    <li>opt out of - 选择退出。    <p>原文例句：Merchants selling on the short video app Douyin can no longer opt out of the option to instantly refund up to US$211 before receiving returned goods.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组由opt（选择）和out of（退出）组成，表示“选择退出”。在这个例句中，它的意思是抖音上的商家不再可以选择退出立即退款至多 211 美元的选项，即使没有收到退回的商品。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>turn off - 关闭，切断。    <p>原文例句：A recent policy update regarding the service introduced in 2021 denies merchants the option of turning it off.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组由turn（转动）和off（关掉）组成，表示“关闭，切断”。在这个例句中，它的意思是最近关于 2021 年推出的这项服务的政策更新，剥夺了商家关闭该选项的权利。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>句子：</h2>  <ul>    <li>Pinduoduo, owned by PDD Holdings, was the first major e-commerce site to introduce a similar refunds policy in 2021 allowing users to get their money back without returning goods found to not match merchant descriptions. - 拼多多是第一个在 2021 年推出类似退款政策的主要电子商务网站，该政策允许用户在发现商品与商家描述不符时无需退货即可拿回退款。<p>句子分析：这是一个复合句，主句是Pinduoduo was the first major e-commerce site to introduce a similar refunds policy，其中主语是Pinduoduo，谓语是was，宾语是the first major e-commerce site to introduce a similar refunds policy。owned by PDD Holdings是一个过去分词短语作定语，修饰Pinduoduo，表示拼多多归 PDD 控股所有。in 2021 allowing users to get their money back without returning goods found to not match merchant descriptions是一个现在分词短语作状语，表示拼多多在 2021 年推出的类似退款政策的内容或方式，即允许用户在发现商品与商家描述不符时无需退货即可拿回退款。这个句子的意思是说，拼多多是第一个在 2021 年推出类似退款政策的主要电子商务网站，该政策允许用户在发现商品与商家描述不符时无需退货即可拿回退款。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>语法：</h2>  <ul>    <li>被动语态 - 表示动作的承受者。    <p>原文例句：The platform operated by Beijing-based ByteDance, which added a shopping channel in 2019, allows users to get a refund as soon as they mail back the returned parcel, rather than when the merchant receives it.</p>    <p>语法讲解：被动语态是一种语态，表示动作的承受者。其结构是：be + 过去分词。在这个例句中，be动词是allows，过去分词是returned，表示退款是由用户获得的。这个句子的意思是说，这家位于北京的字节跳动运营的平台于 2019 年添加了一个购物渠道，该渠道允许用户在寄回退货包裹后立即获得退款，而不是在商家收到包裹后获得退款。</p></li>  </ul>   <ul>    <li>强调句 - 表示强调。    <p>原文例句：This was seen as a major factor in helping Pinduoduo woo price-sensitive Chinese consumers away from competing platforms.</p>    <p>语法讲解：强调句是一种句子，用于强调句子中的某个部分。其结构是：It was/is + 被强调部分 + that/who。在这个例句中，被强调的部分是a major factor in helping Pinduoduo woo price-sensitive Chinese consumers away from competing platforms。这个句子的意思是说，这被视为帮助拼多多从竞争平台吸引对价格敏感的中国消费者的一个主要因素。</p></li>  </ul></div>  <ul><li>Merchants selling on the short video app Douyin can no longer opt out of the option to instantly refund up to US$211 before receiving returned goods</li>
<li>Alibaba’s Taobao and JD.com recently started offering refunds without returns to woo consumers away from rising budget e-commerce champion Pinduoduo</li>
</ul><figure><img src="https://cdn.i-scmp.com/sites/default/files/d8/images/canvas/2024/01/03/3ce8d4ad-d4c8-4569-8e73-e028869c8250_11da8613.jpg" /><figcaption>The logo of Douyin displayed next to a mobile phone displaying an e-commerce site on the app in an illustration picture taken on October 25, 2023. Photo: Reuters</figcaption></figure><p>Douyin, the Chinese version of <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/tiktok" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/topics/tiktok">TikTok</a> that is betting big on <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/ecommerce" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/topics/ecommerce">e-commerce</a>, has made its “express refund” policy mandatory, forcing merchants to immediately return money to consumers upon request to compete with similar offerings on Taobao and Pinduoduo.</p><p>The platform operated by Beijing-based <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/bytedance" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/topics/bytedance">ByteDance</a>, which added a shopping channel in 2019, allows users to get a refund as soon as they mail back the returned parcel, rather than when the merchant receives it. A recent policy update regarding the service introduced in 2021 denies merchants the option of turning it off.</p><p>E-commerce platforms are turning to policies known as “refund without returning the cargo” or “refund without reason” as part of a push to be more consumer-friendly at the expense of merchants amid intensified competition. Online retail sales of tangible goods in China increased 8.3 per cent in the first 11 months of 2023, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3246559/chinese-e-commerce-firms-jdcom-and-alibabas-taobao-roll-out-refund-only-policy-shoppers-heating" title="">JD.com, Alibaba’s Taobao push ‘refund only’ policy to rival Pinduoduo’s strategy</a></h3><p>Budget shopping app <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/pinduoduo" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/topics/pinduoduo">Pinduoduo</a>, owned by PDD Holdings, was the first major e-commerce site to introduce a similar refunds policy in 2021 allowing users to get their money back without returning goods found to not match merchant descriptions. This was seen as a major factor in helping Pinduoduo woo price-sensitive Chinese consumers away from competing platforms.</p><p>The policy of allowing refunds without returns has started to gain favour as platforms look for any possible edge over rivals.</p><p>Taobao, the e-commerce platform from <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/alibaba" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/topics/alibaba">Alibaba Group Holding</a>, and <a href="https://www.scmp.com/topics/jdcom" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/topics/jdcom">JD.com</a> last week rolled out their own <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3246559/chinese-e-commerce-firms-jdcom-and-alibabas-taobao-roll-out-refund-only-policy-shoppers-heating" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3246559/chinese-e-commerce-firms-jdcom-and-alibabas-taobao-roll-out-refund-only-policy-shoppers-heating">“refund only” policies</a>, finally matching the option from Pinduoduo. Alibaba owns the South China Morning Post.</p><p>Douyin has offered refunds without returns since September.</p><p>Douyin’s new refund service is not available for customised products or non-tangible goods such as memberships. Instant refunds are also limited to 1,500 yuan (US$211).</p><div class="methode-html-wrapper oembed-wrapper">
</div><p>Alibaba has been facing a new sense of urgency to win back consumers after PDD overtook China’s e-commerce king in market capitalisation. Alibaba was valued at US$190.2 billion on the New York Stock Exchange on Tuesday, lower than PDD’s US$193.5 billion on the Nasdaq.</p><p>In December, <a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3246060/alibaba-promotes-millennials-key-e-commerce-leadership-roles-it-repositions-fend-rivals" target="_self" title="https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3246060/alibaba-promotes-millennials-key-e-commerce-leadership-roles-it-repositions-fend-rivals">Alibaba promoted six young managers</a> to run its core e-commerce business unit in an attempt to “reignite their entrepreneurial spirit” and “secure and win their future”, according to an internal letter penned by the conglomerate’s CEO Eddie Wu Yongming, two days after he became the head of the unit.</p> ]]></description>
