<title>Samsung to kick off year of AI phones with new launch this month</title>
<link>https://www.scmp.com/tech/tech-trends/article/3247104/samsung-kick-year-ai-phones-new-launch-month</link>
<description><![CDATA[ <div>  <h2>Summary：</h2>  Samsung, the world's largest smartphone manufacturer, is focusing on artificial intelligence (AI) as the key to driving sales growth in 2024. The company plans to launch its next flagship device, the Galaxy S24, on January 17, with a focus on AI capabilities. This shift comes as smartphone makers seek to differentiate their products through AI features, such as generative AI, which can generate text or visual responses to user queries. Samsung aims to capture a significant share of the market for AI-powered smartphones, estimated to reach over a billion units by the end of 2027.  <ul>    <li>Abstract: Samsung emphasizes AI as the key to unlocking greater sales in the smartphone market.</li>    <li>Theme: Samsung's strategic shift towards AI-powered smartphones.</li>    <li>Viewpoint: The growing importance of AI in differentiating smartphones and driving sales.</li>    <li>Main information: Samsung's plans for the Galaxy S24 launch, the potential market size for AI-powered smartphones, and the contributions of OpenAI's generative AI tools.</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>总结：</h2>  三星，全球最大的智能手机制造商，正将人工智能（AI）视为2024年推动销售增长的关键。该公司计划于1月17日在加利福尼亚州圣何塞推出其下一代旗舰设备Galaxy S24，重点是人工智能功能。这种转变正值智能手机制造商寻求通过人工智能功能来区分其产品之际，例如能够对用户查询生成文本或视觉响应的生成式人工智能。三星的目标是占领人工智能智能手机市场的很大份额，据估计，到2027年底将达到超过十亿部。  <ul>    <li>摘要：三星强调人工智能是打开智能手机市场更大销量的关键。</li>    <li>主题：三星向人工智能智能手机的战略转型。</li>    <li>观点：人工智能在区分智能手机和推动销售方面日益重要。</li>    <li>主要信息：三星对Galaxy S24发布的计划、人工智能智能手机的潜在市场规模以及OpenAI的生成式人工智能工具的贡献。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>单词：</h2>  <ul>    <li>generative (adj.) - /ˈdʒɛnərətɪv/ 富有创造力的，能产生创造性成果的。    <p>原文例句：More than a billion smartphones with built-in generative AI are expected to be shipped by the end of 2027, according to Counterpoint Research estimates.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于Latin，由generare（产生，产生）和-tive（形成，产生）组成，表示“有创造力，产生创造性成果”。在这个例句中，它指的是能够产生创造性成果的人工智能，例如能够生成文本或视觉响应的用户查询的人工智能。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>integrate (v.) - /ˈɪntɪɡreɪt/ 集成，融合。    <p>原文例句：The next step in advancing the technology is to integrate it into devices, as US chip maker Qualcomm has touted over the past year.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于Latin，由inter（之间）和gradi（走）组成，表示“使融合，使集成”。在这个例句中，它指的是将技术集成到设备中，例如将人工智能集成到智能手机中。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>promising (adj.) - /ˈprɑːmɪsɪŋ/ 有希望的，有前途的。    <p>原文例句：2024 promises to be a year where added AI capabilities take centre stage.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于Old French，由promettre（承诺，保证）和-ing（表示进行，延续）组成，表示“有希望的，有前途的”。在这个例句中，它指的是2024年有望成为人工智能功能占据中心位置的一年。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>词组：</h2>  <ul>    <li>take centre stage - 成为中心舞台。    <p>原文例句：2024 promises to be a year where added AI capabilities take centre stage.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组是由take（采取），centre（中心）和stage（舞台）组成的，表示“成为中心舞台”。在这个例句中，它指的是2024年人工智能功能有望成为中心舞台。</p></li>  </ul>  </div><div>  <h2>句子：</h2>  <ul>    <li>The teaser to the launch promises only that “Galaxy AI is coming”. - 发布的预告片只承诺“Galaxy AI即将到来”。</li>    <p>句子分析：这是一个简单句，主句是The teaser promises only that “Galaxy AI is coming”.，其中主语是The teaser，谓语是promises，宾语是that “Galaxy AI is coming”.。only that “Galaxy AI is coming”是一个由only和that “Galaxy AI is coming”组成的句子，表示“只承诺Galaxy AI即将到来”。这个句子的意思是说，发布的预告片只承诺“Galaxy AI即将到来”。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>语法：</h2>  <ul>    <li>现在完成时 - 表示从过去某个时间开始一直持续到现在的动作或状态。    <p>原文例句：In past years, Samsung and fellow smartphone makers have relied on improvements in camera technology and flexible displays to stand out.</p>    <p>语法讲解：这是一个时态，结构是：have/has + been + 过去分词。其中have/has要根据主语的人称和数进行变化，been是be的过去分词，过去分词是动词的-ed形式。这种时态表示动作或状态从过去某个时间开始一直持续到现在，强调动作或状态的持续性和未完成性。在这个例句中，它表示三星和其他智能手机制造商在过去的几年中一直依靠相机技术和柔性显示屏的改进脱颖而出。</p></li>  </ul>   <ul>    <li>动名词 - 表示动作或状态的名词。    <p>原文例句：The next step in advancing the technology is to integrate it into devices.</p>    <p>语法讲解：这是一个非限定名词，结构是：动词ing。动名词可以表示动作或状态，可以作主语、宾语、表语、定语或状语。在这个例句中，它表示整合技术到设备中的过程，作主语。</p></li>  </ul></div>  <ul><li>In past years, Samsung and fellow smartphone makers have relied on improvements in camera technology and flexible displays to stand out</li>
<li>More than a billion smartphones with built-in generative AI are expected to be shipped by the end of 2027, according to Counterpoint Research estimates</li>
</ul><p>The world’s most prolific smartphone maker is leaning into artificial intelligence (AI) as the key to unlocking greater sales this year.</p><p>Samsung Electronics announced it plans to launch its next flagship device – likely to be known as the Galaxy S24 – on January 17 in San Jose, California, with a live-streamed event. The teaser to the launch promises only that “Galaxy AI is coming”.</p><p>In past years, Samsung and fellow smartphone makers have relied on improvements in camera technology and flexible displays to stand out, but 2024 promises to be a year where added AI capabilities take centre stage.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/article/3246310/huawei-launches-new-nova-smartphones-without-giving-details-chip-attention-remains-fixed-its" title="">Huawei launches new Nova smartphones without giving details on chip</a></h3><p>More than a billion smartphones with built-in generative AI are expected to be shipped by the end of 2027, according to Counterpoint Research estimates.</p><p>OpenAI’s ChatGPT and Dall-E tools, which generate text or visual responses to users’ queries, are at the forefront of a generative-AI wave that is swept across the tech industry – and helped make Nvidia a trillion-dollar company by providing the key AI-training accelerators. The next step in advancing the technology is to integrate it into devices, as US chip maker Qualcomm has touted over the past year.</p><p>“Samsung and Qualcomm are immediate leaders as current product offerings and capabilities position them as first movers,” the Counterpoint researchers wrote in December. “Similar to what it did with foldables, Samsung is likely to capture almost 50 per cent share for the next two years, followed by key Chinese OEMs like Xiaomi, Vivo, Honor and Oppo.”</p> ]]></description>
</item>

