<title>Montana appealing ruling that blocked state from barring TikTok use</title>
<link>https://www.scmp.com/tech/policy/article/3247089/montana-appealing-ruling-blocked-state-barring-tiktok-use</link>
<description><![CDATA[ <div>  <h2>Summary：</h2>  美国蒙大拿州总检察长奥斯汀·克努森（Austin Knudsen）提交了一份通知，表示该州正在向美国第九巡回上诉法院对判决提出上诉。美国地区法官唐纳德·莫洛伊（Donald Molloy）于 11 月 30 日发布初步禁令，阻止该禁令生效，称蒙大拿州的法律“超越了州权力”。蒙大拿州周二表示，将对美国一名法官 11 月份的决定提出上诉，该法官阻止了该州对使用短视频分享应用程序 TikTok 的首次此类禁令。  <ul>    <li>Abstract: 蒙大拿州就禁止抖音一案提出上诉。</li>    <li>Theme: 蒙大拿州对 TikTok 的禁令引发法律纠纷。</li>    <li>Viewpoint: 联邦政府和州政府在应用程序监管方面的权力分歧；TikTok 在保护用户数据和国家安全方面的责任。</li>    <li>Main information: TikTok禁令被初步阻止；蒙大拿州认为该禁令符合宪法；TikTok 否认与中国政府共享用户数据；联邦政府和多个州已禁止在政府设备上使用 TikTok。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>总结：</h2>  美国蒙大拿州总检察长奥斯汀·克努森（Austin Knudsen）向法院递交了上诉通知，表示该州正在就美国第九巡回上诉法院对TikTok禁令的判决提出上诉。此前，美国地区法官唐纳德·莫洛伊（Donald Molloy）于11月30日发布了初步禁令，以阻止该禁令的生效，并表示蒙大拿州的禁令“以多种方式违反了宪法”和“超越了州权力”。TikTok和克努森的办公室对此尚未发表评论。莫洛伊法官此前表示，初步庭前陈述应在1月16日前提交。TikTok与事实核查员合作，阻止网站上的选举错误信息。去年，蒙大拿州的用户也对该州立法机构批准的禁令提起了诉讼，该禁令援引了对蒙大拿州用户个人数据和潜在中国间谍活动的担忧。在早些时候提交的法庭文件中，TikTok表示“没有，也不会与中国政府共享美国用户的数据，并已采取切实措施保护TikTok用户隐私和安全”。莫洛伊法官表示，蒙大拿州寻求行使联邦政府持有的外交政策权力，该州的行动过于全面。TikTok一直面临着国会中一些人禁止该应用程序或赋予拜登政府实施限制或禁止外国应用程序的权力的努力，但这些努力已陷入僵局。许多州和美国政府已禁止在政府设备上使用TikTok，但只有蒙大拿州试图完全禁止使用该应用程序。前总统唐纳德·特朗普在2020年试图禁止下载TikTok和中国拥有的微信，但一系列法院裁决阻止了该禁令的生效。  <ul>    <li>摘要：蒙大拿州对抖音禁令提出上诉。</li>    <li>主题：蒙大拿州对 TikTok 的禁令引发法律纠纷。</li>    <li>观点：联邦政府和州政府在应用程序监管方面的权力分歧；TikTok 在保护用户数据和国家安全方面的责任。</li>    <li>主要信息：TikTok禁令被初步阻止；蒙大拿州认为该禁令符合宪法；TikTok 否认与中国政府共享用户数据；联邦政府和多个州已禁止在政府设备上使用 TikTok。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>单词：</h2>  <ul>    <li>bar (n.) - /bɑːr/ 酒吧，阻碍，限制。    <p>原文例句：TikTok teams up with fact checkers to stop election disinformation on site</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词由古法语barre（长条，棍子）演变而来，表示“长条形的东西，障碍物”。在这个例句中，它表示“酒吧”。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>preliminary (adj.) - /prɪˈlɪmɪnəri/ 初步的，暂时的。    <p>原文例句：US District Judge Donald Molloy on November 30 issued a preliminary injunction to block the ban, saying Montana’s law ‘oversteps state power’</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来自拉丁语prae（以前）和limen（门槛），表示“在开始之前的，暂时的”。在这个例句中，它表示“初步的”。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>violate (v.) - /ˈvaɪləˌleɪt/ 违反，侵犯。    <p>原文例句：Molloy said Montana sought to exercise foreign policy authority held by the federal government and the state’s action was too sweeping.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来自拉丁语violare（侵犯，伤害），表示“违反，侵犯”。在这个例句中，它表示“违反”。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>词组：</h2>  <ul>    <li>take effect - 生效，起效。    <p>原文例句：Montana’s ban had been set to take effect on January 1, but…</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组由take（拿，取）和effect（效果，影响）组成，表示“生效，起效”。在这个例句中，它表示“生效”。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>be due - 应该，应当。    <p>原文例句：Molloy had previously said preliminary pretrial statements were due by January 16.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组由be（是，存在）和due（到期的，应得的）组成，表示“应该，应当”。在这个例句中，它表示“应该”。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>句子：</h2>  <ul>    <li>TikTok has faced efforts by some in Congress to ban the app or give the Biden administration's powers to impose restrictions or bar foreign-owned apps, but those efforts have stalled.  TikTok一直面临着国会中一些人禁止该应用程序或赋予拜登政府实施限制或禁止外国应用程序的权力的努力，但这些努力已陷入僵局。</li>    <p>句子分析：这是一个复合句，由两个简单句“TikTok has faced efforts by some in Congress to ban the app or give the Biden administration's powers to impose restrictions or bar foreign-owned apps”和“those efforts have stalled”连接而成。第一个简单句的主语是“TikTok”，谓语是“has faced”，宾语是“efforts”。第二个简单句的主语是“those efforts”，谓语是“have stalled”。这个句子的意思是说，TikTok一直面临着国会中一些人禁止该应用程序或赋予拜登政府实施限制或禁止外国应用程序的权力的努力，但这些努力已陷入僵局。</p>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>语法：</h2>  <ul>    <li>分词的用法 - 分词可以作定语、状语和表语。    <p>原文例句：TikTok and Knudsen’s office did not immediately comment.</p>    <p>语法讲解：这个句子中，“comment”是一个现在分词，作状语，表示“立即”。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>被动语态 - 被动语态用于强调动作的承受者。    <p>原文例句：Molloy said Montana sought to exercise foreign policy authority held by the federal government…</p>    <p>语法讲解：这个句子中，“sought”是一个过去分词，作谓语，表示“寻求”。“held”是一个过去分词，作定语，表示“被掌握的”。</p></li>  </ul></div>  <ul><li>Montana Attorney General Austin Knudsen filed a notice that the state is appealing the ruling to the Ninth Circuit US Court of Appeals</li>
<li>US District Judge Donald Molloy on November 30 issued a preliminary injunction to block the ban, saying Montana’s law ‘oversteps state power’</li>
</ul><p>Montana said on Tuesday it was appealing a decision by a US judge in November to block the state's first-of-its kind ban on the use of short-video sharing app TikTok.</p><p>Montana Attorney General Austin Knudsen filed a notice that the state is appealing the ruling to the Ninth Circuit US Court of Appeals.</p><p>Montana’s ban had been set to take effect on January 1, but US District Judge Donald Molloy on November 30 issued a preliminary injunction to block the ban on the Chinese-owned app, saying Montana’s law “violates the Constitution in more ways than one” and “oversteps state power”.</p><p>TikTok and Knudsen’s office did not immediately comment. Molloy had previously said preliminary pretrial statements were due by January 16.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/news/china/politics/article/3246313/taiwan-elections-tiktok-teams-fact-checkers-stop-disinformation-site" title="">TikTok teams up with fact checkers to stop election disinformation on site</a></h3><p>TikTok users in Montana also had filed suit last year to block the ban approved by the state legislature, which cited concerns about the personal data of Montana users and potential Chinese spying.</p><p>In earlier court filings, TikTok said it “has not shared, and would not share, US user data with the Chinese government, and has taken substantial measures to protect the privacy and security of TikTok users”. Molloy said Montana sought to exercise foreign policy authority held by the federal government and the state’s action was too sweeping.</p><p>TikTok has faced efforts by some in Congress to ban the app or give the Biden administration's powers to impose restrictions or bar foreign-owned apps, but those efforts have stalled.</p><p>Many states and the US government have barred TikTok on government-owned devices, but only Montana has sought to completely bar the app’s use.</p><p>Former President Donald Trump in 2020 sought to bar new downloads of TikTok and Chinese-owned WeChat, but a series of court decisions blocked the effective ban from taking effect.</p> ]]></description>
</item>

