<title>Apple hits 7-week low after Barclays downgrade on demand concerns</title>
<link>https://www.scmp.com/tech/big-tech/article/3247083/apple-hits-seven-week-low-after-barclays-downgrade-demand-concerns</link>
<description><![CDATA[ <div>  <h2>Summary：</h2>  Apple's shares saw a significant increase of nearly 50 percent in 2023, reaching a record high in mid-December. However, recent concerns about weakening demand, particularly for the iPhone and Mac devices, have led to a 3.6 percent drop in Apple's shares on Tuesday. Barclays downgraded the company's stock due to these concerns, making it the second brokerage to issue a "sell" rating. This has contributed to a rise in bearish recommendations for Apple, reaching the highest number in at least two years.  <ul>    <li>Abstract: Apple's share performance in 2023, recent decline due to demand concerns, and analyst recommendations.</li>    <li>Theme: Apple's stock market performance in the context of overall market trends.</li>    <li>Viewpoint: Barclays' downgrade of Apple's stock highlights the shifting market sentiment towards the company.</li>    <li>Main information: Apple's share rise in 2023, holiday-quarter sales forecast below expectations, concerns about iPhone and Mac demand, and Barclays' "underweight" rating.</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>总结：</h2>  苹果公司的股票在2023年上涨了近50%，并在12月中旬创下历史新高，当时科技巨头引领了市场。自去年年初以来，该公司一直在努力应对需求放缓，并预测假日季度的销售额低于华尔街的预期。周二，苹果股价下跌近3.6%，创下七周新低，此前巴克莱将这家全球最有价值公司的股票评级下调，原因是担心该公司从iPhone到Mac的设备需求在2024年仍将疲软。巴克莱是第二家给予该股票相当于“卖出”评级的经纪公司，根据LSEG的数据，该股票现在至少两年内收到的看跌建议最多。该股票占标普500指数市值权重的7%，周二大盘指数被拉低了0.56%。苹果在2023年上涨了近50%，并在12月中旬创下历史新高，当时科技巨头引领了市场。苹果公司正在加快Vision Pro的生产，目标是2月份上市。自去年年初以来，苹果一直在努力应对需求放缓，并预测假日季度的销售额低于华尔街的预期。在本土竞争对手华为技术公司复兴后，其在中国市场的表现也令人担忧。“iPhone 15一直表现不佳，我们认为iPhone 16应该也是如此，”巴克莱分析师蒂姆·朗在一份客户报告中表示，他指出中国的疲软以及发达市场的需求疲软。根据LSEG的数据，朗在苹果推荐准确度方面的评级为五星中的四星。该经纪公司还警告称，苹果的服务业务正面临越来越大的风险，该业务在美国等国家因应用商店做法而受到审查。近年来，该业务经常超过苹果硬件部门的增长，现在占公司总收入的近四分之一。苹果将在专利纠纷中对美国手表的禁令提出上诉。周二的大跌抹去了苹果公司超过1000亿美元的市值，其股价收于185.64美元。在周二之前，自2022年7月以来，伊陶BBA的“卖出”是唯一看跌苹果的评级。分析师平均将这家iPhone制造商评级为“买入”，目标价中值为200美元。该公司按其未来12个月的预期收益计算的市盈率约为28.7倍，远高于标普500指数的19.8倍。  <ul>    <li>摘要：苹果公司在2023年的股票表现、由于需求担忧导致的近期下跌以及分析师建议。</li>    <li>主题：苹果公司股票市场表现的整体市场趋势背景。</li>    <li>观点：巴克莱下调苹果股票评级凸显了市场对该公司的态度转变。</li>    <li>主要信息：苹果公司在2023年的股价上涨、假日季度的销售额预测低于预期、对iPhone和Mac需求的担忧以及巴克莱的“减持”评级。</li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>单词：</h2>  <ul>    <li>rout (n.) - /raʊt/ 大败，溃败。    <p>原文例句：The stock rout on Tuesday erased more than US$100 billion of Apple’s market capitalisation, as its shares closed at US$185.64.</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于古法语，原意为“哄闹，喧闹”，引申为“大败，溃败”。在这个例句中，它指的是周二的股市大跌，导致苹果公司的市值蒸发了超过1000亿美元，其股票收于185.64美元。</p></li>  </ul>  <ul>    <li>scanner (n.) - /ˈskænə/ 扫描仪。    <p>原文例句：The business has come under the scanner in countries including the United States over app store practices. </p>    <p>例句讲解：这个单词来源于拉丁语，原意为“爬行，探索”，引申为“扫描仪”。在这个例句中，它指的是苹果公司的服务业务在美国等国家因应用商店做法而受到审查。</p></li>  </ul>  </div><div>  <h2>词组：</h2>  <ul>    <li> holiday-quarter - 假日季度    <P>原文例句：Apple has been grappling with a demand slowdown since early last year and has forecast holiday-quarter sales below Wall Street estimates</p>    <p>例句讲解：这个词组指的是圣诞节和新年期间的销售旺季，通常是从11月到12月。在这个例句中，它指的是苹果公司预测假日季度的销售额低于华尔街的预期。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>句子：</h2>  <ul>    <li>Apple rose nearly 50 per cent in 2023, hitting a record high in mid-December in a year when Big Tech companies led the markets. </li>    <p>句子分析：这是一个复句，由两个简单句组成，主句是Apple rose，宾语是从句hitting a record high in mid-December in a year when Big Tech companies led the markets。 hitting a record high in mid-December in a year when Big Tech companies led the markets是一个过去分词短语作状语，修饰主句Apple rose，表示苹果公司在2023年上涨了近50%，并在12月中旬创下历史新高。in a year when Big Tech companies led the markets是一个时间状语从句，修饰hitting a record high，表示在科技巨头引领市场的一年中。这个句子的意思是说，苹果公司在2023年上涨了近50%，并在12月中旬创下历史新高，当时科技巨头引领了市场。</p></li>  </ul></div><div>  <h2>语法：</h2>  <ul>    <li>定语从句 - 用于修饰或限定名词或代词。    <p>原文例句：Investors are cheering Apple’s strong performance in 2023, when the company’s shares rose nearly 50 per cent. </p>    <p>语法讲解：这是一个定语从句，由when the company’s shares rose nearly 50 per cent组成，修饰名词performance，表示投资者对苹果公司在2023年的强劲表现感到欢呼雀跃，当时该公司的股票上涨了近50%。在这个例句中，定语从句是一个时间状语从句，表示在苹果公司股票上涨近50%的时候。</p></li>  </ul>    <ul>    <li>现在完成式 - 表示从过去某个时间开始一直持续到现在的动作或状态。    <p>原文例句：Since early last year, Apple has been grappling with a demand slowdown. </p>    <p>语法讲解：这是一个现在完成式的句子，由have been grappling with a demand slowdown组成，其中have been是助动词，grappling with a demand slowdown是现在分词。现在完成式表示从过去某个时间开始一直持续到现在的动作或状态，强调动作或状态的持续性和未完成性。在这个例句中，它表示自去年年初以来，苹果公司一直在努力应对需求放缓的情况。</p></li>  </ul></div>  <ul><li>Apple’s shares rose nearly 50 per cent in 2023, hitting a record high in mid-December in a year when Big Tech firms led the markets</li>
<li>The company has been grappling with a demand slowdown since early last year and has forecast holiday-quarter sales below Wall Street estimates</li>
</ul><p>Apple on Tuesday fell nearly 3.6 per cent to a seven-week low after Barclays downgraded the shares of the world’s most valuable company on concerns that demand for its devices, from the iPhone to the Mac, will remain weak in 2024.</p><p>Barclays is the second brokerage to have the equivalent of a “sell” rating on the stock, which now has its most number of bearish recommendations in at least two years, according to LSEG data.</p><p>The stock accounts for a hefty 7 per cent of the S&amp;P 500’s market weight – the broader index was dragged 0.56 per cent lower on Tuesday.</p><p>Apple rose nearly 50 per cent in 2023, hitting a record high in mid-December in a year when Big Tech companies led the markets.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/tech/tech-trends/article/3245817/apple-ramps-vision-pro-production-aiming-launch-february" title="">Apple ramps up Vision Pro production, aiming for launch by February</a></h3><p>Apple has been grappling with a demand slowdown since early last year and has forecast holiday-quarter sales below Wall Street estimates. Its performance in China has also been a worry after the revival of local rival Huawei Technologies.</p><p>“The iPhone 15 has been lacklustre and we believe iPhone 16 should be the same,” Barclays analyst Tim Long said in a client note, pointing to the China weakness as well as subdued demand in developed markets.</p><p>Long is rated four out of five stars for his recommendation accuracy on Apple, according to LSEG data.</p><p>The brokerage also warned risks were mounting for Apple’s services business, which has come under the scanner in countries including the United States over app store practices.</p><p>The business has often outpaced growth in Apple’s hardware segment in recent years and now accounts for nearly a quarter of the company’s total revenue.</p><h3><a href="https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3246322/us-import-ban-certain-apple-watch-models-takes-effect-over-patent-clash" title="">Apple to appeal US watch ban in patent dispute</a></h3><p>The stock rout on Tuesday erased more than US$100 billion of Apple’s market capitalisation, as its shares closed at US$185.64.</p><p>Barclays downgraded the stock to “underweight” from “neutral” and trimmed its 12-month price target by US$1 to US$160. Before Tuesday, Itau BBA’s “sell” was the only bearish rating on Apple since July 2022.</p><p>Analysts, on average, rate the iPhone maker “buy”, with a median price target of US$200. The company trades at about 28.7 times its 12-month forward earnings estimates, much higher than the S&amp;P 500’s 19.8.</p> ]]></description>
